75 % of professional working mothers have been problems as a result of their babies
discrimination in the workplace has risen in recent years , especially for the women of the young people who want to be mothers .
that reveals the study " fertility and women 's professional career in spain , " carried out by the csic in collaboration with the instituto de la mujer .
the survey , conducted on 9 737 women from 15 to 75 years , that leaves no room for doubt : 75 percent of working mothers have seen their careers limited because of the babies .
the study indicates that there are many differences regarding the beginning of life in a partnership , and the number of children , whether or not the woman is occupied and the kind of job .
those who do not have to work outside the home , work part time , or have a stable job little , they are earlier in a partnership , and have more children have their first pregnancy earlier .
however , women who have a stable job , mostly in the public sector , postpone the entry in life in a partnership , and the first pregnancy , and having fewer children .
women aged between 35 and 49 with fixed work have their first child , on average , 3.7 years after having built in couple . that figure rises to 4.1 among those who work in the public sector . " these data show that women have a stable job was needed for more time in their lives for that , which led them to reject the union and the arrival of the children .
more broadly , the type of job exercised influence the babies , but not the starting date of cohabitation , " explains the csic 's chercheuse margarita delgado .
the level of education is another factor that widening the gap in the age of the marriage of women and their first child .
according to the survey , the higher the level of training is , the more they are marient , and have their first child later .
the difference is also maintains among the women of the same generation .
for example , in a group of between 35 and 49 years , those who have made elementary and higher studies have been mothers respectively for the first time in 25,1 and 32,1 years on average .
" another disctinction is also among the women , according to their level of education .
while those who carry out the basic studies are marient and have their first child had to find a stable job , those studies of higher average level or reverse the programme and give priority to the achievement of a stable work as a condition for marriage and the arrival of a child , " says mrs delgado .
