michelin and fesvial , sets to the wearing of the headphones
the tyre manufacturer michelin , in cooperation with the spanish foundation for road safety , fesvial , has launched a campaign to encourage the wearing of the helmet , mainly among motorcyclists youngsters , as we have said today the two bodies .
this initiative aims to promote awareness of the importance of the wearing of the helmet , because it is the only part of protection to avoid head injuries , or even death , in case of an accident in two wheels .
michelin said that the campaign was in keeping with his commitment to road safety , which goes beyond the design and manufacture of products increasingly safe " and said that it is contributing to this goal by other actions to educational and informative .
this new campaign to encourage the port of the helmet with two wheels , under the motto " to be but not to be , " a first stage in which include posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages in effect , in order to guarantee the widest spread .
finally , michelin pointed out that the road safety is a constant concern for the company , because as a tyre manufacturer for vehicles on two wheels , one of its main objectives is to develop products increasingly safe .
the sale of light commercial vehicles to go
after nearly two years ago , the light commercial vehicle market is starting to see a little bit of light at the end of the tunnel .
the 9 425 vehicles registered in november in spain represent an increase of 12.6 % compared to 2008 and , what is more important , they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive month of decline , according to the figures by the patronal manufacturers association anfac and ganvam , the dealers .
however , we need to qualify the good news , as the reference for the comparison , the month of november 2008 , was particularly bad , with a reduction of 60 % in comparison with the previous year .
as a result , despite the events of the last month , the immatriculations accumulated during the 11 months are 40 % in less than those of the previous year .
since january , if we add all vehicles coming into the category of light commercial vehicles - derived from cars and light pick-up , vans , fourgons and light trucks to windows 95 853 have been sold .
high clouds that affect the more their request did not eliminated . in fact , despite being bought by individuals , most of the purchases are made by small and medium sized enterprises , which pay in nearly 100 % of the cases thanks to an external financing .
as well , in addition to the restrictions involved by limiting the bank credits , we need to add other factors such as the rise in the unemployment rate and the persistence of the bad economic situation .
faced with this situation and in contrast to the cars , support for the purchase of the 2000e were used .
as well as individuals , independent and those who wish to acquire a commercial vehicle slightly less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of carbon dioxide emissions , which does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre , can also benefit from it , but the number of operations speaks for itself .
