the dealers ' association provides a 2010 similar to that ends , to which it is a fall in sales , in private cars and the suv of 19 % .
aid to the emergency brake is now required
as it has been done with the system anti-lock brakes abs and it will take place with the stability control esp , emergency aid for brake systems will be compulsory element on european cars .
mandatory they are already on the newly registered passenger cars and light commercial vehicles , while for the rest of the vehicles , a period has been set up at the end of february 2011 .
the measure , imposed by the european union , is intended to strengthen the protection of pedestrians , even if , because of its course of action , it can also help prevent many back shocks .
the assistant to the emergency brake is increasing the pressure on the brakes in urgent cases detected by the system through the shot in the foot by the driver .
but they do not always keeps the pressure until the end of time .
according to a study conducted by the manufacturer of components for cars bosch , one third of the drivers involved in an accident did not rely on the brakes before the collision , and half of them did not benefit from its full force .
up to 1 , 100 accidents
the intervention of the aid , revancha , requires maximum of the brake system , reducing the distance the car needs to stop .
according to a study by the eu , if all vehicles were equipped with this type of " points , up to 1 100 fatal accidents in which pedestrians are involved could be prevented each year .
the reduction would be even more important with the popularisation of ' smart emergency braking systems : it is a sinister about four with the injured would be avoided .
in this case , the vehicle is equipped with a system that , thanks to a radar or a camera , detect the obstacles and prevents the slightly driver , in addition to act on the brakes .
when the driver is applied , it help in increasing the pressure on the , if it is necessary .
if it does not act and , even though the collision is inevitable , it is the maximum effort on the brakes in order to minimize the damage .
