estimate by garage in four stages
with the auda-taller tool , the company audatex ensures that the user gets an estimate in just four stages : identifying the vehicle , seek the room to spare , creating an estimate and the engineer .
the ease of use is a key element of these systems , especially in order to convince the older workers who , to a greater or lesser extent , are resistant to the use of new technologies of management .
the database includes 1 034 vehicles , including tourism , 109 tout-terrains 666 , 137 motorbikes , 78 , vans and 44 lorries .
naturally , in order to use it , a computer and a connection to the internet are necessary .
once the model to repair identified thanks to its actual number of windows , a graphic image of the model in question is can you selects the piece needed .
the user can include variables such as the price of the workforce , supplements or reduced , and then it can give the estimate for the return to the customer .
audataller is not a tool to estimate as a audaplus , but a catalogue of benchmarks .
the main difference between the two systems is that one for the garages do not include the estimated time of workforce .
the cost of using this tool in the garage of 350 euros per year , which can be the subject of credit .
at the moment , the company audatex works so that these pictures are in three dimensions .
this is something that engineers are a very positive because it will , for example , to select a door and make it look to see the face internal .
